<subSubSection id="79DA65243627FC05C482D99AFC10B772" pageId="30" pageNumber="395" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="317F36AF3627FC05C482D99AFC10B772" blockId="30.[178,1085,1189,1407]" pageId="30" pageNumber="395">
Comment: Like 
<taxonomicName id="F6C04D2C3627FC05C5A9D999FD8BB6B6" box="[409,548,1189,1211]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicornis">
<emphasis id="03B4EABD3627FC05C5A9D999FD8BB6B6" box="[409,548,1189,1211]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="395">O. flavicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F6C04D2C3627FC05C602D999FD60B6B6" baseAuthorityName="MANNERHEIM" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[562,719,1189,1211]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haemorrhoa">
<emphasis id="03B4EABD3627FC05C602D999FD60B6B6" box="[562,719,1189,1211]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="395">O. haemorrhoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is extremely variable. In particular, this is true of the shape of the antennae, which may occasionally approach the condition in 
<taxonomicName id="F6C04D2C3627FC05C4E4D9E1FEC8B6FE" box="[212,359,1245,1267]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicornis">
<emphasis id="03B4EABD3627FC05C4E4D9E1FEC8B6FE" box="[212,359,1245,1267]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="395">O. flavicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In one locality in northern 
<collectingCountry id="49D7763F3627FC05C682D9E2FD51B6FE" box="[690,766,1245,1267]" name="Turkey" pageId="30" pageNumber="395">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, both species were collected together. Based on external characters alone, it was virtually impossible to distinguish them. A reliable identification, however, is unproblematic based on the sexual characters, especially the shape and internal structures of the median lobe of the aedeagus. For an illustration of the aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName id="F6C04D2C3627FC05C5CFD871FD0EB76E" baseAuthorityName="MANNERHEIM" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[511,673,1357,1379]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haemorrhoa">
<emphasis id="03B4EABD3627FC05C5CFD871FD0EB76E" box="[511,673,1357,1379]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="395">O. haemorrhoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<bibRefCitation id="55514B5E3627FC05C6E8D872FCD9B76E" author="ASSING V" box="[728,886,1357,1379]" pageId="30" pageNumber="395" pagination="1301 - 1325" refId="ref19990" refString="ASSING V. (2008): Nine new species and additional records of Staphylinidae from southern Spain, with new synonymies (Insecta: Coleoptera). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 40 (2): 1301 - 1325." type="journal article" year="2008">ASSING (2008)</bibRefCitation>
. In one Moroccan locality, 
<taxonomicName id="F6C04D2C3627FC05C53BD855FE08B772" baseAuthorityName="MANNERHEIM" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[267,423,1385,1407]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haemorrhoa">
<emphasis id="03B4EABD3627FC05C53BD855FE08B772" box="[267,423,1385,1407]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="395">O. haemorrhoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected together with the similar 
<taxonomicName id="F6C04D2C3627FC05C70BD855FC16B772" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2008" box="[827,953,1386,1407]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imminuta">
<emphasis id="03B4EABD3627FC05C70BD855FC16B772" box="[827,953,1386,1407]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="395">O. imminuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
